In Google Chrome using the Rapid Board -> Plan tab, I cannot see the last word of the issue summary in the Backlog. When clicking on an issue I can see the full title.

It only happens on Chrome. Firefox and IE works like a charm.

See attached screenshots

The new *Rapid Board* caters for the users to have cross-projects in it. However, the following error appears if one or more projects are missing the *Administer Projects* permission.

{noformat}
Project Administrator permissions are required to add a sprint
{noformat}

The solution to this matter is to ensure that the project(s) that are to be included in the sprint has the rightful permission. However, it could be quite troublesome for the user if the are managing a lot of projects. They will have to manually check one by one and it is time consuming.

In this case, rather than just having the message displayed when hovering on the disabled *Start Sprint* button as mentioned before,
it would be really convenient and better *GreenHopper* can check on the lack of *Project Permission* and tell the users know on what projects are missing the *Administer Project* permission. A suggestion would be something like:

{noformat}
The Administer Project permission(s) are required for the following project(s):
- Project A
- Project B
- Project C
{noformat}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-5614].
  {panel}

It would be a great improvement if we could see the Sub-tasks Estimation in main task on the Plan Mode of the Rapid Board.

Currently, we are only able to see the main issue estimation, and if we only add estimations to the sub-tasks, no estimations are displayed are all.
